## Experimental Requirement and Novelty

This proposal requires that the experimental setup be tested **explicitly as defined**, using two physically identical double-slit barriers, which-path detection only at the first slit, asymmetric enhancement on Path B (longer distance + weak detector/scatterer), and controlled single- and two-particle regimes.

To the best of the author’s knowledge, this exact sequential double-slit configuration with asymmetric Path B enhancement has not been explicitly tested in published literature. Results should not be inferred solely from analogous systems but verified through direct measurement.
